    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1866-08-06T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1866-08-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="227"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d227">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Sir F.
                        Bruce</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic"
                                >Washington</hi>,</placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1866-08-06">
                            <hi rend="italic">August</hi> 6, 1866.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> Referring to my communication of the 16th of July
                    last, and to your note of the same month, upon the subject of the detention of
                    James Diamond in the Old Jail at Toronto, I have now the honor to enclose, for
                    the consideration of her Majesty’s government in Canada, additional evidence in
                    the favor of Mr. Diamond, who, it appears, has been, previous to his capture by
                    the Canadian authorities, a faithful soldier in the service of the United
                    States.</p>
                <p>Requesting you to return the original papers to me after you have satisfied
                    yourself as to their contents,</p>
                <p>I have the honor to be, with the highest consideration, sir, your obedient
                    servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>The Hon. Sir <hi rend="smallcaps">Frederick W. A. Bruce</hi>, <hi
                            rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
